Brazil Coffee Exports Fall 18 Percent in July, Ministry Says

-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 
2011-08-01T18:45:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/brazil-coffee-exports-fall-18-percent-in-july-ministry-says.html
Coffee exports from  Brazil , the
world’s largest producer and exporter of the bean, slumped 18
percent in July from a year ago, Brazil’s Trade Ministry said.  Shipments were 1.81 million bags, down from 2.2 million
bags a year earlier, the ministry said today in a report on its
website.  A bag of coffee weighs 60 kilograms.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in  Sao Paulo  at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net . 